Interface ApplicationRequestArrivalI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.interfaces.ComponentImplementedI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.OfferedI, java.rmi.Remote, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.RequiredI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.TwoWayI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApplicationRequestArrivalInboundPort, ApplicationRequestGeneratorOutboundPort, ApplicationRequestServiceConnector

    public interface ApplicationRequestArrivalI
extends fr.upmc.components.interfaces.TwoWayI
    The interface ApplicationRequestArrivalI defines the protocol to send an application upload request

    Description

    The interface can be both required and offered, and it has only one method acceptApplication passing a Application object as parameter.
